e239d5669ea348af914454c805f70e33.output: "Lord, I am small, and so is the one ring I am to carry, but its evil is much greater than me. I will leave Middle-earth for the Mountains of Shadow, with my uncle Bilbo; he is much better suited than I for this task. May the Eagles be with me on my journey to Mount Doom, even as I fear the dark places from which no light can escape. No night will befall me so deep that I cannot find the dawn. And remember, even if this seems like a great burden, I must complete it in hope that may bring light to all the peoples of Middle-earth. There is much pain ahead, but as the One gives the strength to fight it, so, too, do I accept everything that may come on my way. Yet, ultimately, like the ring, this journey is about freedom, for those who would end its rule over us."
